Additional Terms and Acknowledgments:

This software contains code and documentation for integrating Arcam AVR 
audio/video receivers with Home Assistant. The integration is provided as 
open source software for the benefit of the Home Assistant community.

Device Protocol License:
The binary protocol implementation is based on publicly available documentation
and reverse engineering efforts. No proprietary Arcam intellectual property is
included in this software. Users must own compatible Arcam devices to use this
integration.

Third-Party Acknowledgments:
- Home Assistant framework (Apache License 2.0)
- Python standard library (Python Software Foundation License)
- Testing frameworks and development tools (various open source licenses)

Trademark Notice:
"Arcam" is a trademark of Arcam (Harman International). This software is not
affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Arcam or Harman International.
The integration is provided as an independent, community-developed solution.

Support and Warranty:
This software is provided on an "AS IS" basis. The authors and contributors
make no warranties, express or implied, regarding the software's functionality,
reliability, or suitability for any particular purpose. Users assume all risks
associated with the use of this software.

No Official Support:
This integration is not officially supported by Arcam, Harman International, or
the Home Assistant organization. Support is provided on a best-effort basis by
the open source community through GitHub issues and discussions.

Limitation of Liability:
In no event shall the authors, contributors, or copyright holders be liable for
any direct, indirect, incidental, special, exemplary, or consequential damages
(including, but not limited to, procurement of substitute goods or services;
loss of use, data, or profits; or business interruption) however caused and on
any theory of liability, whether in contract, strict liability, or tort
(including negligence or otherwise) arising in any way out of the use of this
software, even if advised of the possibility of such damage.

Device Safety:
Users are responsible for ensuring the safe operation of their Arcam devices.
This software sends commands to network-connected audio/video equipment. Users
should verify that volume levels, power states, and other device settings are
appropriate for their environment before using automation features.

Privacy and Data Collection:
This integration operates entirely on the local network and does not collect,
transmit, or store any personal data outside of the user's Home Assistant
installation. All device communication remains within the user's local network.

Compliance:
Users are responsible for ensuring their use of this software complies with all
applicable local laws and regulations regarding network device control and home
automation systems.

Source Code Availability:
The complete source code for this integration is available at:
https://github.com/CSdread/arcam-control-home-assistant

For questions about licensing, please create an issue on the GitHub repository.

